From: Hemanth Pasupuleti <satyasaihemanth.p@utdallas.edu>
Subject: [PATCH] Allow unexpected dropout_prob_by_embodiment key when loading N1.7 checkpoint

The released nvidia/GR00T-H-N1.7 checkpoint contains
'action_head.dropout_prob_by_embodiment' but the d8369db code no longer
defines this parameter in Gr00tN1d7. The existing allowlist only covers
the reverse (model has the key, checkpoint doesn't). Add the symmetric
case so the checkpoint key is silently ignored on load.

Upstream issue: code/weights mismatch in NVIDIA-Medtech/GR00T-H d8369db.
Apply with: git apply patches/groot_h/001-allow-unexpected-dropout-prob-key.patch
Remove when upstream fixes the mismatch.

--- a/gr00t/model/gr00t_n1d7/setup.py
+++ b/gr00t/model/gr00t_n1d7/setup.py
@@ -102,6 +102,8 @@ class Gr00tN1d7Pipeline(ModelPipeline):
             allowed_missing_keys = {"action_head.dropout_prob_by_embodiment"}
             missing_keys = [key for key in missing_keys if key not in allowed_missing_keys]
             unexpected_keys = loading_info.get("unexpected_keys", [])
+            allowed_unexpected_keys = {"action_head.dropout_prob_by_embodiment"}
+            unexpected_keys = [key for key in unexpected_keys if key not in allowed_unexpected_keys]
             mismatched_keys = loading_info.get("mismatched_keys", [])
             errors = []
             if missing_keys:
